  "executive_brief_md": "## PDCD1 \u2014 programmed cell death 1\n\n**White Space score 0.0/100 \u00b7 rank 13/13 \u00b7 HIGH confidence.** Saturated floor \u2014 validated and tractable but maximally crowded. The calibration anchor.\n\nPDCD1 is a cell membrane ; single-pass type i membrane protein target in the immuno-oncology cohort with 7 approved agent(s) (Cemiplimab, Dostarlimab, Nivolumab, Pembrolizumab\u2026). Development level **Tclin**; mechanism: Programmed cell death protein 1 antagonist; Programmed cell death protein 1 inhibitor. Competitive footprint: 44 industry sponsor(s) in trials. Leading disease associations: melanoma, non-small cell lung carcinoma, renal cell carcinoma, esophageal squamous cell carcinoma.\n\n**Score decomposition** \u2014 Validation 0.6284, Tractability 1.0, Saturation 1.0 (cohort-normalized). The score is multiplicative, so crowding drives it down even when biology is validated \u2014 which is why saturated checkpoints sit low and validated-but-uncrowded targets rise.\n\n*Every figure above resolves to a versioned source in the Provenance tab. This brief is model-written (claude-fable-5) over sourced facts only.*",
